---
// Static Astro component - About section
const skills = [
    "React",
    "Next.js",
    "TypeScript",
    "Node.js",
    "Tailwind CSS",
    "SQL",
    "MySQL",
    "PHP",
    "Laravel",
    "Firebase",
    "Godot",
    "C",
    "C#",
    "Bun",
    "ElysiaJS",
    "Turso",
];
---

<section id="about" class="py-20 bg-gray-900">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
            <h2
                class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12 text-white"
            >
                My <span class="text-rose-400">Story</span>
            </h2>

            <div class="text-center max-w-4xl mx-auto">
                <div class="space-y-6">
                    <p class="text-gray-300 text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed">
                        Konnichiwa! I'm just your everyday code isekai
                        protagonist, turning coffee into web magic faster than a
                        shounen hero powers up. I don't just write code; I cast
                        spells on the digital realm, and it bends to my will. My
                        specialty is creating websites with technologies
                        straight out of a sci-fi anime.
                    </p>

                    <p class="text-gray-300 text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed">
                        When I'm not grinding on my latest project, you can find
                        me contemplating the philosophy of bugs, arguing with my
                        AI waifu about the true meaning of `null`, or slapping
                        more anime stickers on my rig—each one a power-up for my
                        coding abilities.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-16">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-center mb-8 text-white">
                    The Current <span class="text-rose-400">Stack We Use</span>
                </h3>
                <div
                    class="bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-700 text-center"
                >
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                        This portfolio is built using modern and powerful technologies to ensure it is blazing fast and reliable. Here is the current stack we use:
                    </p>
                    <ul
                        class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-gray-400 list-none text-left max-w-md mx-auto"
                    >
                        <li>
                            <span class="text-rose-400 font-semibold"
                                >Framework:</span
                            > Powered by <span class="font-medium text-white"
                                >Astro & React</span
                            >, blending SSG performance with interactive islands.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <span class="text-rose-400 font-semibold"
                                >Styling:</span
                            > Painted with <span class="font-medium text-white"
                                >Tailwind CSS</span
                            >, keeping the UI slick and developer experience fast.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <span class="text-rose-400 font-semibold"
                                >Language:</span
                            > Written in <span class="font-medium text-white"
                                >TypeScript</span
                            >, for type safety and rock-solid autocomplete.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <span class="text-rose-400 font-semibold"
                                >Database:</span
                            > Connected to <span class="font-medium text-white"
                                >Turso (libSQL)</span
                            >, managing the live guestbook seamlessly.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <span class="text-rose-400 font-semibold"
                                >Mailing Service:</span
                            > Hooked up with <span class="font-medium text-white"
                                >Resend</span
                            >, handling messages directly from the contact form.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-16">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-center mb-8 text-white">
                    My <span class="text-rose-400">Skill Tree</span>
                </h3>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 justify-center">
                    {
                        skills.map((skill) => (
                            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-rose-400/10 text-rose-400 rounded-full text-sm border border-rose-400/20">
                                {skill}
                            </span>
                        ))
                    }
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
